-- Developer Loans Limited to 50% of Project Value, Securities Times Reports
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-04T22:47:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-04/developer-loans-limited-to-50-of-project-value-securities-times-reports.html
Chinese regulators have ordered banks
to limit loans to real estate developers to 50 percent of a
property project’s value, the Securities Times reported today,
citing unidentified people.  Of China’s 60 large property developers, 18 have debt to
equity ratios of 70 percent or more, the newspaper reported.
Loans taken by the 60 large property developers that reach
maturity by the end of 2012 equals 64 percent of the total value
of their loans, according to the report. Loans by the 60 large
developers that reach maturity within the next year account for
28 percent, according to the report.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
 jliu42@bloomberg.net  